        %h1 Privacy Policy
        %p
          We understand that your privacy is important to you. We are committed to respecting your privacy and protecting your personally-identifiable information (being any information that may reasonably identify you as an individual person) as you use McKinsey Academy and this Site. The scope of our commitment is described in this Privacy Policy.
        %hr

        %p
          “McKinsey Academy” includes this website 
          %a{href: '/'}
            http://www.mckinseyacademy.com
          (the “Site”) and any related courses, programs, services, materials or offerings provided by us either through or in connection with the Site. McKinsey Academy is provided by McKinsey & Company, Inc. United States and its affiliates (“us”, “our” or “we”) for your (“you”) use, subject to the Terms of Use applicable to McKinsey Academy, which are available at 
          %a{href: '/terms'}
            http://www.mckinseyacademy.com/terms
          (the “Terms”).
        %p
          By submitting personally-identifiable information, you consent to our use of your information as described herein and in the Terms. The Terms include more information about our provision of McKinsey Academy in general and we encourage you to review them. Capitalized terms that are used in this Privacy Policy and are not otherwise defined have the same definition given to them in the Terms.
        %p.style-2 What personally-identifiable information is collected?
        %p
          McKinsey collects personally-identifiable information on certain areas of the Site when users register, access or use McKinsey Academy or McKinsey Academy Content, including use of course content, submission of User Content and participation in user posting areas (such as bulletin boards, discussion forums and surveys). The personally-identifiable information collected may consist of information that you provide, such as your name, e-mail address, and other User Account Information. In addition, McKinsey Academy may collect certain other information you do not visibly enter or intentionally provide that is not necessarily personally identifying, but could become identified with you, such as your IP address, browsing, viewing or other usage data in connection with your use of McKinsey Academy and the Site, click stream data, HTTP protocol elements, and the status of cookies placed on your computer by McKinsey or by our third party licensors or content providers.
        %p.style-2 How may McKinsey use my personally-identifiable information?
        %p
          We use your personally-identifiable information to provide you with the McKinsey Academy services you request, including enabling you to access courses and McKinsey Academy Content through the Site, and to contact you either directly or through the Site about McKinsey Academy in order to provide support, important information or otherwise to help improve your user experience. 
        %p
          We may also use your personally-identifiable information (including your User Account Information), as well as your User Content, to (a) verify your identity and your eligibility to use the Site or participate in other aspects of McKinsey Academy; (b) communicate with you about McKinsey Academy, including your participation in any courses or other services offered through the Site; (c) with your consent, allow other users to communicate with you about McKinsey Academy, including your participation in any courses or other services offered through the Site; (d) provide, administer and improve McKinsey Academy, the Site and the McKinsey Academy Content, including administering courses and services in which you participate, providing user support, course progress and assessment grading, and integrating McKinsey Academy, the Site and McKinsey Academy Content with platforms, content and services provided by third parties (including edX) as part of the McKinsey Academy experience; and (e) develop and improve, and contact you about, McKinsey Academy and the Site, including to solicit your feedback and to identify other courses or services provided by us that may be of interest to you. If you prefer not to receive non-essential communications from us about McKinsey Academy, including information about future courses or service offerings, please email support@mckinseyacademy.com.
        %p
          Your personally-identifiable information may also be used, both by us and by our authorized third party service providers (including edX), to collect, discover, and prepare aggregate statistical and volume information, and other similar data, including with respect to the number, characteristics, behavior, and performance of McKinsey Academy, users of and visitors to the Site, and users of McKinsey Academy Content (collectively, “Aggregate Site Information”). We may use, and permit our authorized third party service providers to use, this Aggregate Site Information in order to administer the Site, for research purposes and to further develop, improve and promote McKinsey Academy and the Site, or for any other purpose provided that such use would not be reasonably likely to result in your identification and is not prohibited by applicable law. We or our authorized third party service providers may use persistent cookies to help us collect and use such Aggregate Site Information, as well as to help us improve the visitor and user experience, manage McKinsey Academy and McKinsey Academy Content, and track visitor and user behavior. We may retain all Aggregate Site Information, even if derived or developed from your User Account Information or User Content, indefinitely.
        %p.style-2 What information does McKinsey Academy share with my employer?
        %p
          If you are participating in McKinsey Academy as part of an employer-sponsored program, at the request of your employer we may provide your employer information about your activities and performance in connection with McKinsey Academy, including grades and other performance information with respect to particular McKinsey Academy courses or services. McKinsey shall not be responsible or liable for the use of such information by your employer, and such use shall be subject to your employer’s policies (including privacy policies) applicable to you.
        %p.style-2 How are cookies used?
        %p
          Cookies are small packets of information that are stored by your web browser. They are put on your web browser by the websites that you visit. These packets of information do not contain personal information about you but they do allow us to know if you visit the same website twice or if you visit related websites.
        %p
          The laws in many European Union countries require you to provide a form of consent before cookies are placed on your web browser unless the cookie is necessary for the website to work.
        %p
          There is no agreed standard for how companies comply with these laws. We do the following:
        %ul.info
          %li
            We only use cookies where they are necessary for our services or where you have provided your express or implied consent.
          %li
            We respect your wishes, and you can inspect, delete, or block any cookies used by us by selecting the appropriate control in your web browser.
          %li
            We support technologies that have been developed and are being developed for your web browser that allows you to be more selective about the cookies that your web browser will accept.
        %p.style-2 What are “cookies” used for on this Site?
        %p
          This Site uses cookies to identify you and your interests and to track your use of the Site. We also use cookies to control access to certain McKinsey Academy Content and to process any requests that you make with us.
        %p
          We may also contract with a third party to send e-mail or other types of communications to Users. To help measure and improve the effectiveness of such communications, the third party may set cookies. Any data collected in connection with such services would be used by the third party solely by or on behalf of McKinsey Academy and shared externally only on an anonymous, aggregated basis.
